#. <section class="sutta" id="mn53"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn53:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 53"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 53"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: Sekhasutta → sekha­paṭi­padā­suttaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn53:0.2"
msgid "Sekhasutta"
msgstr "A Trainee"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.354"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "mn53:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "mn53:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near "
"Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. VAR: anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ → anajjhāvutthaṃ (bj, km, pts1) | anaj­jhā­vuṭṭha­pubbaṃ (s1-3)
#. VAR: acirakāritaṃ → acirakāritaṃ hoti (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn53:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ navaṃ santhāgāraṃ "
"acirakāritaṃ hoti anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā kenaci vā "
"manussabhūtena."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time a new town hall had recently been constructed for the "
"Sakyans of Kapilavatthu. It had not yet been occupied by an ascetic or "
"brahmin or any person at all."

msgctxt "mn53:2.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho "
"kāpilavatthavā sakyā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to "
"one side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn53:2.3"
msgid ""
"“idha, bhante, kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ navaṃ santhāgāraṃ acirakāritaṃ "
"anajjhāvuṭṭhaṃ samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā kenaci vā manussabhūtena."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, a new town hall has recently been constructed for the Sakyans of "
"Kapilavatthu. It has not yet been occupied by an ascetic or brahmin or any "
"person at all."

msgctxt "mn53:2.4"
msgid ""
"Taṃ, bhante, bhagavā paṭhamaṃ paribhuñjatu. Bhagavatā paṭhamaṃ paribhuttaṃ "
"pacchā kāpilavatthavā sakyā paribhuñjissanti."
msgstr ""
"May the Buddha be the first to use it, and only then will the Sakyans of "
"Kapilavatthu use it."

msgctxt "mn53:2.5"
msgid "Tadassa kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"That would be for the lasting welfare and happiness of the Sakyans of "
"Kapilavatthu.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:3.1"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence."

#. VAR: sabbasanthariṃ santhāgāraṃ → sabbasanthariṃ santhataṃ (bj, mr)
msgctxt "mn53:3.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena navaṃ santhāgāraṃ "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā sabbasanthariṃ santhāgāraṃ santharitvā "
"āsanāni paññapetvā udakamaṇikaṃ upaṭṭhapetvā telappadīpaṃ āropetvā yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing that the Buddha had accepted, the Sakyans got up from their "
"seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right. "
"Then they went to the new town hall, where they spread carpets all over, "
"prepared seats, set up a water jar, and placed a lamp. Then they went back "
"to the Buddha"

msgctxt "mn53:3.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu."
msgstr "bowed, stood to one side,"

msgctxt "mn53:3.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "and told him of their preparations, saying:"

msgctxt "mn53:3.5"
msgid ""
"“sabbasanthariṃ santhataṃ, bhante, santhāgāraṃ, āsanāni paññattāni, "
"udakamaṇiko upaṭṭhāpito, telappadīpo āropito."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn53:3.6"
msgid "Yassadāni, bhante, bhagavā kālaṃ maññatī”ti."
msgstr "“Please, sir, come at your convenience.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghena yena "
"santhāgāraṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā pāde pakkhāletvā santhāgāraṃ "
"pavisitvā majjhimaṃ thambhaṃ nissāya puratthābhimukho nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the new town "
"hall together with the Saṅgha of mendicants. Having washed his feet he "
"entered the town hall and sat against the central column facing east."

msgctxt "mn53:4.2"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhusaṃghopi kho pāde pakkhāletvā santhāgāraṃ pavisitvā pacchimaṃ bhittiṃ "
"nissāya puratthābhimukho nisīdi, bhagavantaṃyeva purakkhatvā."
msgstr ""
"The Saṅgha of mendicants also washed their feet, entered the town hall, and "
"sat against the west wall facing east, with the Buddha right in front of "
"them."

msgctxt "mn53:4.3"
msgid ""
"Kāpilavatthavāpi kho sakyā pāde pakkhāletvā santhāgāraṃ pavisitvā "
"puratthimaṃ bhittiṃ nissāya pacchimābhimukhā nisīdiṃsu, bhagavantaṃyeva "
"purakkhatvā."
msgstr ""
"The Sakyans of Kapilavatthu also washed their feet, entered the town hall, "
"and sat against the east wall facing west, with the Buddha right in front of "
"them."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:5.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā kāpilavatthave sakye bahudeva rattiṃ dhammiyā kathāya "
"sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"The Buddha spent most of the night educating, encouraging, firing up, and "
"inspiring the Sakyans with a Dhamma talk. Then he addressed Venerable Ānanda:"

#. VAR: pāṭipado → paṭipado (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn53:5.2"
msgid "“paṭibhātu taṃ, ānanda, kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ sekho pāṭipado."
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, speak about the practicing trainee to the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu "
"as you feel inspired."

msgctxt "mn53:5.3"
msgid "Piṭṭhi me āgilāyati;"
msgstr "My back is sore,"

msgctxt "mn53:5.4"
msgid "tamahaṃ āyamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "I’ll stretch it.”"

msgctxt "mn53:5.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "mn53:5.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññāpetvā dakkhiṇena passena "
"sīhaseyyaṃ kappesi, pāde pādaṃ accādhāya, sato sampajāno, uṭṭhānasaññaṃ "
"manasi karitvā."
msgstr ""
"And then the Buddha spread out his outer robe folded in four and lay down in "
"the lion’s posture—on the right side, placing one foot on top of the other—"
"mindful and aware, and focused on the time of getting up."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Ānanda addressed Mahānāma the Sakyan:"

msgctxt "mn53:6.2"
msgid ""
"“idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sīlasampanno hoti, indriyesu guttadvāro hoti, "
"bhojane mattaññū hoti, jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti, sattahi saddhammehi "
"samannāgato hoti, catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ "
"diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī."
msgstr ""
"“Mahānāma, a noble disciple is accomplished in ethics, guards the sense "
"doors, eats in moderation, and is committed to wakefulness. They have seven "
"good qualities, and they get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in "
"the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without "
"trouble or difficulty."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.355"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:7.1"
msgid "Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sīlasampanno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a noble disciple accomplished in ethics?"

msgctxt "mn53:7.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati "
"ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati "
"sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple is ethical, restrained in the monastic code, and "
"has appropriate behavior and means of collecting alms. Seeing danger in the "
"slightest flaw, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "mn53:7.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sīlasampanno hoti. (1)"
msgstr "That’s how a noble disciple is ethical."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:8.1"
msgid "Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako indriyesu guttadvāro hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a noble disciple guard the sense doors?"

msgctxt "mn53:8.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti "
"nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple sees a sight with the eyes, they don’t get caught up "
"in the features and details."

msgctxt "mn53:8.3"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati "
"cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "mn53:8.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "mn53:8.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "mn53:8.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "mn53:8.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …"
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "mn53:8.8"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"When they know a phenomenon with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the "
"features and details."

msgctxt "mn53:8.9"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati "
"manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of mind was left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "mn53:8.10"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako indriyesu guttadvāro hoti. (2)"
msgstr "That’s how a noble disciple guards the sense doors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:9.1"
msgid "Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako bhojane mattaññū hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a noble disciple eat in moderation?"

msgctxt "mn53:9.2"
msgid "Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako paṭisaṅkhā yoniso āhāraṃ āhāreti:"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant reflects properly on the food that they eat."

msgctxt "mn53:9.3"
msgid ""
"‘neva davāya na madāya na maṇḍanāya na vibhūsanāya; yāvadeva imassa kāyassa "
"ṭhitiyā yāpanāya vihiṃsūparatiyā brahmacariyānuggahāya. Iti purāṇañca "
"vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me bhavissati "
"anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro cā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to continue and "
"sustain this body, avoid harm, and support spiritual practice. So that I "
"will put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and "
"so that I will keep on living blamelessly and at ease.’"

msgctxt "mn53:9.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako bhojane mattaññū hoti. (3)"
msgstr "That’s how a noble disciple eats in moderation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:10.1"
msgid "Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a noble disciple committed to wakefulness?"

msgctxt "mn53:10.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako divasaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi "
"cittaṃ parisodheti, "
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant practices walking and sitting meditation by day, "
"purifying their mind from obstacles. "

msgctxt "mn53:10.3"
msgid ""
"rattiyā paṭhamaṃ yāmaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ "
"parisodheti, "
msgstr ""
"In the evening, they continue to practice walking and sitting meditation. "

msgctxt "mn53:10.4"
msgid ""
"rattiyā majjhimaṃ yāmaṃ dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappeti, pāde pādaṃ "
"accādhāya, sato sampajāno, uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi karitvā, "
msgstr ""
"In the middle of the night, they lie down in the lion’s posture—on the right "
"side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on "
"the time of getting up. "

msgctxt "mn53:10.5"
msgid ""
"rattiyā pacchimaṃ yāmaṃ paccuṭṭhāya caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi "
"cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"In the last part of the night, they get up and continue to practice walking "
"and sitting meditation, purifying their mind from obstacles."

msgctxt "mn53:10.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti. (4)"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is committed to wakefulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.356"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:11.1"
msgid "Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a noble disciple have seven good qualities?"

msgctxt "mn53:11.2"
msgid "Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has faith in the Realized One’s awakening:"

msgctxt "mn53:11.3"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:12.1"
msgid ""
"Hirimā hoti, hirīyati kāyaduccaritena vacīduccaritena manoduccaritena, "
"hirīyati pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā."
msgstr ""
"They have a conscience. They’re conscientious about bad conduct by way of "
"body, speech, and mind, and conscientious about having any bad, unskillful "
"qualities."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:13.1"
msgid ""
"Ottappī hoti, ottappati kāyaduccaritena vacīduccaritena manoduccaritena, "
"ottappati pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā."
msgstr ""
"They exercise prudence. They’re prudent when it comes to bad conduct by way "
"of body, speech, and mind, and prudent when it comes to acquiring any bad, "
"unskillful qualities."

#. VAR: dhātā → dhatā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: bahussutā → bahū sutā (?)
msgctxt "mn53:13.2"
msgid ""
"Bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo. Ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā "
"majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthā sabyañjanā kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ "
"parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti "
"dhātā vacasā paricitā manasānupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā."
msgstr ""
"They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These "
"teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the "
"end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s "
"entirely full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering "
"them, reinforcing them by recitation, mentally scrutinizing them, and "
"comprehending them theoretically."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:15.1"
msgid ""
"Āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and "
"gaining skillful qualities. They’re strong, firmly applied, not slacking off "
"when it comes to developing skillful qualities."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:16.1"
msgid ""
"Satimā hoti, paramena satinepakkena samannāgato, cirakatampi cirabhāsitampi "
"saritā anussaritā."
msgstr ""
"They’re mindful. They have utmost mindfulness and alertness, and can "
"remember and recall what was said and done long ago."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:17.1"
msgid ""
"Paññavā hoti, udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato, ariyāya nibbedhikāya "
"sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"They’re wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is "
"noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering."

msgctxt "mn53:17.2"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti. (5–11)"
msgstr "That’s how a noble disciple has seven good qualities."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:18.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, mahānāma, ariyasāvako catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ "
"diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a noble disciple get the four absorptions—blissful meditations "
"in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without "
"trouble or difficulty?"

msgctxt "mn53:18.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, mahānāma, ariyasāvako vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a noble disciple, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded "
"from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption …"

msgctxt "mn53:18.3"
msgid ""
"vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati;"
msgstr "second absorption …"

msgctxt "mn53:18.4"
msgid "pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati;"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "mn53:18.5"
msgid ""
"sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ "
"atthaṅgamā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "mn53:18.6"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ "
"diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī. "
"(12–15.)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how a noble disciple gets the four absorptions—blissful meditations "
"in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without "
"trouble or difficulty."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.357"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:19.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako evaṃ sīlasampanno hoti, evaṃ indriyesu "
"guttadvāro hoti, evaṃ bhojane mattaññū hoti, evaṃ jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti, "
"evaṃ sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti, evaṃ catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ "
"ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī "
"akasiralābhī, ayaṃ vuccati, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sekho pāṭipado "
"apuccaṇḍatāya samāpanno, bhabbo abhinibbhidāya, bhabbo sambodhāya, bhabbo "
"anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya."
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple is accomplished in ethics, guards the sense doors, "
"eats in moderation, and is committed to wakefulness; and they have seven "
"good qualities, and they get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in "
"the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without "
"trouble or difficulty, they are called a noble disciple who is a practicing "
"trainee. Their eggs are unspoiled, and they are capable of breaking out of "
"their shell, becoming awakened, and achieving the supreme sanctuary."

msgctxt "mn53:19.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, mahānāma, kukkuṭiyā aṇḍāni aṭṭha vā dasa vā dvādasa vā tānāssu "
"kukkuṭiyā sammā adhisayitāni sammā pariseditāni sammā paribhāvitāni, kiñcāpi "
"tassā kukkuṭiyā na evaṃ icchā uppajjeyya:"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a chicken with eight or ten or twelve eggs. And she "
"properly sat on them to keep them warm and incubated. Even if that chicken "
"doesn’t wish:"

msgctxt "mn53:19.3"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatime kukkuṭapotakā pādanakhasikhāya vā mukhatuṇḍakena vā aṇḍakosaṃ "
"padāletvā sotthinā abhinibbhijjeyyun’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘If only my chicks could break out of the eggshell with their claws and beak "
"and hatch safely!’ "

msgctxt "mn53:19.4"
msgid ""
"atha kho bhabbāva te kukkuṭapotakā pādanakhasikhāya vā mukhatuṇḍakena vā "
"aṇḍakosaṃ padāletvā sotthinā abhinibbhijjituṃ."
msgstr "Still they can break out and hatch safely."

msgctxt "mn53:19.5"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, mahānāma, yato ariyasāvako evaṃ sīlasampanno hoti, evaṃ "
"indriyesu guttadvāro hoti, evaṃ bhojane mattaññū hoti, evaṃ jāgariyaṃ "
"anuyutto hoti, evaṃ sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti, evaṃ catunnaṃ "
"jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti "
"akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, ayaṃ vuccati, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sekho "
"pāṭipado apuccaṇḍatāya samāpanno, bhabbo abhinibbhidāya, bhabbo sambodhāya, "
"bhabbo anuttarassa yogakkhemassa adhigamāya."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a noble disciple is practicing all these things they "
"are called a noble disciple who is a practicing trainee. Their eggs are "
"unspoiled, and they are capable of breaking out of their shell, becoming "
"awakened, and achieving the supreme sanctuary."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:20.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, mahānāma, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"āgamma anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati,"
msgstr ""
"Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble "
"disciple recollects their many kinds of past lives."

msgctxt "mn53:20.2"
msgid ""
"seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ "
"anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, "
msgstr ""
"That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a "
"hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world "
"contracting, many eons of the world evolving, many eons of the world "
"contracting and evolving. … And so they recollect their many kinds of past "
"lives, with features and details. "

msgctxt "mn53:20.3"
msgid "ayamassa paṭhamābhinibbhidā hoti kukkuṭacchāpakasseva aṇḍakosamhā. (1)"
msgstr "This is their first breaking out, like a chick from an eggshell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:21.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, mahānāma, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"āgamma dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati "
"cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate … pe … "
"yathākammūpage satte pajānāti, "
msgstr ""
"Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble "
"disciple, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, sees sentient "
"beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and "
"ugly, in a good place or a bad place. … They understand how sentient beings "
"are reborn according to their deeds. "

msgctxt "mn53:21.2"
msgid "ayamassa dutiyābhinibbhidā hoti kukkuṭacchāpakasseva aṇḍakosamhā. (2)"
msgstr "This is their second breaking out, like a chick from an eggshell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.358"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:22.1"
msgid ""
"Sa kho so, mahānāma, ariyasāvako imaṃyeva anuttaraṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"āgamma āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati, "
msgstr ""
"Relying on this supreme purity of mindfulness and equanimity, that noble "
"disciple realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in "
"this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due "
"to the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "mn53:22.2"
msgid "ayamassa tatiyābhinibbhidā hoti kukkuṭacchāpakasseva aṇḍakosamhā. (3)"
msgstr "This is their third breaking out, like a chick from an eggshell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
#. VAR: Yampi → yampi kho (bj, mr)
msgctxt "mn53:23.1"
msgid ""
"Yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sīlasampanno hoti, idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple’s conduct includes the following: being accomplished in "
"ethics,"

msgctxt "mn53:23.2"
msgid ""
"yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako indriyesu guttadvāro hoti, idampissa hoti "
"caraṇasmiṃ;"
msgstr "guarding the sense doors,"

msgctxt "mn53:23.3"
msgid ""
"yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako bhojane mattaññū hoti, idampissa hoti "
"caraṇasmiṃ;"
msgstr "moderation in eating,"

msgctxt "mn53:23.4"
msgid ""
"yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti, idampissa hoti "
"caraṇasmiṃ;"
msgstr "being committed to wakefulness,"

msgctxt "mn53:23.5"
msgid ""
"yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako sattahi saddhammehi samannāgato hoti, idampissa "
"hoti caraṇasmiṃ;"
msgstr "having seven good qualities,"

msgctxt "mn53:23.6"
msgid ""
"yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ "
"diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, "
"idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"and getting the four absorptions when they want, without trouble or "
"difficulty."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:24.1"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho, mahānāma, ariyasāvako anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, "
"seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ "
"anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, idampissa hoti vijjāya;"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple’s knowledge includes the following: recollecting their past "
"lives,"

msgctxt "mn53:24.2"
msgid ""
"yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena "
"satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate "
"duggate … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti, idampissa hoti vijjāya."
msgstr "clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman,"

msgctxt "mn53:24.3"
msgid ""
"Yampi, mahānāma, ariyasāvako āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ "
"paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja "
"viharati, idampissa hoti vijjāya."
msgstr ""
"and realizing the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this "
"very life due to the ending of defilements."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:25.1"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, mahānāma, ariyasāvako vijjāsampanno itipi caraṇasampanno itipi "
"vijjācaraṇasampanno itipi."
msgstr ""
"This noble disciple is said to be ‘accomplished in knowledge’, and also ‘"
"accomplished in conduct’, and also ‘accomplished in knowledge and conduct’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:25.2"
msgid "Brahmunāpesā, mahānāma, sanaṅkumārena gāthā bhāsitā:"
msgstr "And Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra also spoke this verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:25.3"
msgid "‘Khattiyo seṭṭho janetasmiṃ,"
msgstr "‘The aristocrat is best of those people"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn53:25.4"
msgid "ye gottapaṭisārino;"
msgstr "who take clan as the standard."

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn53:25.5"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampanno,"
msgstr "But one accomplished in knowledge and conduct"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn53:25.6"
msgid "so seṭṭho devamānuse’ti."
msgstr "is best of gods and humans.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:25.7"
msgid ""
"Sā kho panesā, mahānāma, brahmunā sanaṅkumārena gāthā sugītā no duggītā, "
"subhāsitā no dubbhāsitā, atthasaṃhitā no anatthasaṃhitā, anumatā "
"bhagavatā”ti."
msgstr ""
"And that verse was well sung by Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra, not poorly sung; well "
"spoken, not poorly spoken, beneficial, not harmful, and it was approved by "
"the Buddha.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:26.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā uṭṭhahitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha got up and said to Venerable Ānanda:"

msgctxt "mn53:26.2"
msgid "“sādhu sādhu, ānanda, "
msgstr "“Good, good, Ānanda! "

msgctxt "mn53:26.3"
msgid ""
"sādhu kho tvaṃ, ānanda, kāpilavatthavānaṃ sakyānaṃ sekhaṃ pāṭipadaṃ "
"abhāsī”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s good that you spoke to the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu about the practicing "
"trainee.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.359"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn53:26.4"
msgid "Idamavocāyasmā ānando."
msgstr "This is what Venerable Ānanda said,"

msgctxt "mn53:26.5"
msgid "Samanuñño satthā ahosi."
msgstr "and the teacher approved."

msgctxt "mn53:26.6"
msgid "Attamanā kāpilavatthavā sakyā āyasmato ānandassa bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr ""
"Satisfied, the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu were happy with what the Venerable "
"Ānanda said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn53:26.7"
msgid "Sekhasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
